    "revised_D": [
      4,
      16,
      128
    ],
    "drivers": [
      "D=256 is construction-infeasible at P in {32,256} (centered_harmonics needs P>=2D, i.e. P>=512); in the original {4,32,256}x{32,256,2048} grid this is 3 infeasible (D,P) pairs (32,32),(256,32),(256,256) = 6 cross-structure cell-measurements per L_d_main.",
      "D=256 is also outside the PRE-A/PRE-D-validated D range (PRE swept D in {4,16,64}; max 64)."
    ],
    "log_spacing": "x4 (4->16) then x8 (16->128); original was uniform x8 (4->32->256).",
    "infeasible_remaining": "1 unique pair (D=128,P=32) = 2 cross-structure cell-measurements per L_d_main; dropped -> not_characterised.",
    "pre_a_range_fact_check": "CORRECTION to the drafted note 'stays within PRE-A's validated range': D=128 is NOT within PRE-A's validated D range (PRE max D=64). Only D=4 and D=16 are. D=128 is out-of-range and is the reason sub-phase 1.0 ran the stability smokes at D=128 (and P in {32,2048}) \u2014 all trained stably (no NaN/Inf), justifying the extension.",
    "decision_reference": "Phase 1 first-session design chat (2026-05-21/22); see v2/PHASE1_PROGRESS.md"
  },
